<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-03-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-03-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="1305" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1305">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">774.00/3–2554: Telegram</note>
                            <head>No. 1305<lb/><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Egypt (<persName corresp="#p_CJ1" type="from">Caffery</persName>) to the
                                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d1305fn1">Repeated to London as telegram 386 and
                                    unnumbered to the Arab capitals, Tel Aviv, Tripoli, and
                                    Khartoum.</note></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-03-25">March 25, 1954</date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>1167. Following lengthy meeting with <persName corresp="#p_NGM1">Naguib</persName> presiding, <gloss target="#t_RCC1">RCC</gloss> announced today following decisions:</p>
                            <list>
                                <label>1.</label>
                                <item>Political parties will be permitted organize
                                    immediately.</item>
                                <label>2.</label>
                                <item><gloss target="#t_RCC1">RCC</gloss> will not form political
                                    party.</item>
                                <pb facs="0543" n="2245" xml:id="pg_2245"/>
                                <label>3.</label>
                                <item>No one will be deprived of political rights.</item>
                                <label>4.</label>
                                <item>Constituent Assembly will be freely elected (no
                                    appointees).</item>
                                <label>5.</label>
                                <item><gloss target="#t_RCC1">RCC</gloss> will turn over all powers
                                    to Constituent Assembly on July 24 and consider revolution
                                    ended. President of Republic will be elected by Assembly when it
                                    meets.</item>
                            </list>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_CJ1"><hi rend="strong"><hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi></hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>